---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Agent Ready checks whether a repository is ready for coding agents."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <title>AGENT READY</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Agent Ready home">
        <img class="brand-mark" src="/favicon.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
        AGENT READY
      </a>
      <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
        <a href="/commands/">Commands</a>
        <a href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a href="#checks">Checks</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="header-actions">
        <a class="header-github" href="https://github.com/carloss765/agent-ready">GitHub</a>
        <a class="header-command-link" href="/commands/">Commands</a>
        <a href="#credits">Built by Carlos</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content">
      <section class="hero" id="top" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
        <canvas id="ascii-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
        <div class="hero-content">
          <p class="eyebrow">Repository readiness for coding agents</p>
          <div class="hero-wordmark">
            <h1 id="hero-title">AGENT READY</h1>
          </div>
          <p class="hero-lede">
            Check whether a project has the context, commands, safety files, and agent tooling it
            needs before you delegate work to Codex, Claude Code, OpenCode, Cursor, or Windsurf.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-command" role="group" aria-label="Command to run Agent Ready">
            <span>$</span>
            <code id="hero-command-text">npx @agent-ready/cli scan</code>
            <button
              class="copy-button"
              type="button"
              data-copy-command="npx @agent-ready/cli scan"
              aria-describedby="copy-status"
            >
              Copy
            </button>
          </div>
          <p class="copy-status" id="copy-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
          <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Primary actions">
            <a class="button button-primary" href="#install">Install CLI</a>
            <a class="button button-secondary" href="/commands/">See commands</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-terminal" id="preview" aria-label="Agent Ready scan output preview">
          <div class="terminal-top" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="window-control window-close"></span>
            <span class="window-control window-minimize"></span>
            <span class="window-control window-maximize"></span>
          </div>
          <pre><code><span class="terminal-muted">$</span> npx @agent-ready/cli scan
<span class="terminal-muted">.. Scanning repository...</span>

Agent readiness
  Score: <span class="terminal-ok">100/100 ██████████</span>
  Status: <span class="terminal-ok">Ready</span>

Tool use
  <span class="terminal-ok">✓ Codex: ready AGENTS.md, .agents</span>
  <span class="terminal-danger">✕ Claude Code: missing</span>
  <span class="terminal-danger">✕ OpenCode: missing</span>

Next steps
  - This repository is ready for coding agents.</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="principles" aria-label="MVP principles">
        <div>
          <strong>No API keys</strong>
          <span>Agent Ready runs locally and does not call a model provider.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>No risky fixes</strong>
          <span>It diagnoses, writes safe base files, and creates a prescription.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Your agent executes</strong>
          <span>Use the generated instructions with the coding agent you already trust.</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-split command-section" id="commands">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Commands</p>
          <h2>Run one command, then choose the next step.</h2>
          <p>
            Agent Ready starts with a read-only scan. If the repository is missing context, use
            `init` to create safe base files or `prescribe` to generate instructions for your coding
            agent.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="run-demo" aria-label="Animated command run preview">
          <canvas id="command-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
          <pre class="run-demo-fallback" aria-hidden="true"><code><span class="terminal-muted">$</span> npx @agent-ready/cli scan
<span class="terminal-muted">.. Scanning repository...</span>
<span class="terminal-ok">✓ README.md found</span>
<span class="terminal-ok">✓ package.json found</span>
<span class="terminal-danger">✕ AGENTS.md missing</span>

<span class="terminal-muted">$</span> npx @agent-ready/cli init
<span class="terminal-ok">✓ Created AGENTS.md</span>
<span class="terminal-ok">✓ Created .env.example</span>

<span class="terminal-muted">$</span> npx @agent-ready/cli prescribe
<span class="terminal-ok">✓ Created .agent-ready/prescription.md</span></code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="command-grid">
          <article>
            <code>npx @agent-ready/cli scan</code>
            <h3>Diagnose readiness</h3>
            <p>Scores the repository and reports missing files, scripts, agent tools, and skills.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <code>npx @agent-ready/cli init</code>
            <h3>Create safe base files</h3>
            <p>Adds missing Agent Ready starter files without overwriting existing project files.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <code>npx @agent-ready/cli prescribe</code>
            <h3>Generate the agent brief</h3>
            <p>Writes a focused prescription your coding agent can follow on the next run.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-split" id="workflow">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
          <h2>Diagnose, initialize, prescribe.</h2>
        </div>
        <ol class="workflow-list">
          <li>
            <span>scan</span>
            <p>Read the repository and score its readiness without modifying files.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>init</span>
            <p>Create missing base files such as AGENTS.md and .env.example without overwrites.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>prescribe</span>
            <p>Generate a focused prompt that tells your coding agent what to fix next.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="checks">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Checks</p>
          <h2>Signals that reduce agent guesswork.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="check-grid">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Context</h3>
            <p>README, AGENTS.md, architecture notes, safety rules, and environment examples.</p>
            <ul class="scan-list" aria-label="Context check examples">
              <li class="scan-ok">✓ README.md found</li>
              <li class="scan-danger">✕ AGENTS.md missing</li>
              <li class="scan-danger">✕ .env.example missing</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Commands</h3>
            <p>Development, build, test, lint, and format scripts that make verification clear.</p>
            <ul class="scan-list" aria-label="Command check examples">
              <li class="scan-ok">✓ build script found</li>
              <li class="scan-ok">✓ lint script found</li>
              <li class="scan-danger">✕ test script missing</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Agent tools</h3>
            <p>Codex, Claude Code, OpenCode, Cursor, Windsurf, and local skill directories.</p>
            <ul class="scan-list" aria-label="Agent tool check examples">
              <li class="scan-ok">✓ Codex ready</li>
              <li class="scan-danger">✕ Claude Code missing</li>
              <li class="scan-danger">✕ OpenCode missing</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section proof-section">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Output</p>
          <h2>A copyable diagnosis for the next agent run.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="output-grid">
          <pre><code>Found
  <span class="scan-ok">✓ README.md</span>
  <span class="scan-ok">✓ package.json</span>
  <span class="scan-ok">✓ Git repository</span>

Missing
  <span class="scan-danger">✕ AGENTS.md</span>
  <span class="scan-danger">✕ .env.example</span>
  <span class="scan-danger">✕ test script</span>

Prescription
  .agent-ready/prescription.md</code></pre>
          <p>
            Agent Ready does not pretend to be the agent. It prepares the repo so the next agent
            has fewer assumptions to make and a clear verification path to follow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="install" id="install" aria-labelledby="install-title">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Install</p>
          <h2 id="install-title">Run it from any repository.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="command-row">
          <code>npx @agent-ready/cli scan</code>
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://github.com/carloss765/agent-ready">
            View GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="credits" id="credits" aria-labelledby="credits-title">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Credits</p>
          <h2 id="credits-title">Built by Carlos.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="credits-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/carloss765">Creator GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/carloss765/agent-ready">Project repository</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>Agent Ready by Carlos</span>
      <a href="https://github.com/carloss765/agent-ready">GitHub repository</a>
    </footer>

    <script>
      import "../scripts/ascii-canvas";
      import "../scripts/command-run-canvas";
      import "../scripts/copy-command";
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
